idable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20this%20is%20where%20things%20get%20tricky.%20The%20Pakistan%20Tehreek-e-Insaf%2C%20or%20PTI%20%E2%80%93%20headed%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-india-19844270%5C%22%3Ejailed%20former%20prime%20minister%20and%20Pakistani%20cricket%20hero%20Imran%20Khan%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20has%20emerged%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2024%2F2%2F10%2Fwhat-comes-next-2%5C%22%3Elargest%20party%20in%20the%20national%20assembly%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20around%2093%20candidates%20winning%20seats%20as%20%E2%80%9Cindependents.%E2%80%9D%20They%20had%20to%20run%20as%20independents%20because%20the%20party%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.voanews.com%2Fa%2Fpakistan-s-pti-barred-from-using-cricket-bat-electoral-symbol-%2F7439552.html%5C%22%3Ebarred%20from%20using%20its%20electoral%20symbol%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20cricket%20bat%2C%20after%20a%20three-member%20bench%20of%20the%20supreme%20court%20ruled%20that%20PTI%20had%20failed%20to%20hold%20intraparty%20elections%20in%20line%20with%20its%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20with%20a%20total%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fasia-pacific%2Fpakistan-vote-counts-drags-after-election-marred-by-attacks-outages-2024-02-09%2F%5C%22%3E265%20seats%20in%20parliament%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that%20means%20the%20PTI%20is%20still%20well%20short%20of%20the%20number%20needed%20to%20form%20a%20government%20on%20its%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Pakistan%20Muslim%20League-Nawaz%2C%20or%20PMLN%2C%20came%20in%20second%20with%2078%20seats%2C%20a%20tally%20that%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20boosted%20by%20the%20addition%20of%20PMLN-aligned%20independent%20members%20of%20parliament.%20The%20party%20%E2%80%93%20headed%20by%20Shahbaz%20Sharif%2C%20who%20took%20over%20from%20Khan%20as%20prime%20minister%20in%202022%2C%20and%20his%20brother%2C%20former%20three-time%20prime%20minister%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20%E2%80%93%20is%20thought%20to%20have%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Finternational%2Fworld-news%2Fpakistan-army-chief-backs-ex-pm-nawaz-sharifs-call-to-form-coalition-government%2Farticleshow%2F107587628.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ebacking%20of%20the%20powerful%20Pakistani%20army%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20it%20did%20not%20perform%20as%20well%20as%20expected%20in%20the%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Pakistan%20People%E2%80%99s%20Party%2C%20or%20PPP%2C%20secured%2054%20seats%2C%20placing%20it%20third.%20This%20puts%20it%20in%20a%20position%20to%20help%20another%20party%20form%20a%20coalition%20at%20the%20federal%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWith%20the%20most%20seats%2C%20is%20the%20PTI%20the%20front-runner%20to%20lead%20a%20coalition%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20PTI%20has%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20it%20wants%20to%20form%20a%20government%20on%20its%20own%20and%20believes%20that%20its%20mandate%20was%20stolen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20before%20the%20final%20election%20results%20became%20known%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fimran-khans-party-claims-victory-in-170-seats-vows-to-form-government-report-5032101%5C%22%3EPTI%20claimed%20it%20had%20won%20170%20or%20so%20seats%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20enough%20for%20it%20to%20be%20able%20to%20form%20a%20government.%20But%20that%20appears%20to%20be%20without%20evidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20suggests%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2Fliveblog%2F2024%2F2%2F11%2Fpakistan-election-results-live-wait-for-final-tally-three-days-after-vote%5C%22%3EPTI%20isn%E2%80%99t%20ready%20to%20accept%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20did%20not%20get%20enough%20votes%20to%20form%20a%20government%20outright.%20The%20party%20instead%20is%20challenging%20the%20results%2C%20claiming%20that%20its%20vote%20was%20suppressed%20illegally%2C%20and%20the%20PTI%20has%20already%20formally%20registered%20complaints%20in%2018%20cons