20of%20a%20selection%20committee%20comprising%20the%20prime%20minister%20as%20its%20chairperson%2C%20a%20union%20cabinet%20minister%20nominated%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20and%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%20as%20its%20member.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20section%20goes%20against%20a%20judgment%20by%20a%20five-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20apex%20court%20in%20March%202022%20which%20had%20disapproved%20of%20the%20system%20brought%20in%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20and%20suggested%20that%20the%20selection%20committee%20includes%20the%20PM%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20Opposition%20and%20the%20chief%20justice%20of%20India%20(CJI).%20It%20was%20aimed%20at%20insulating%20the%20government%20of%20the%20day%20to%20influence%20appointment%20of%20top%20officials%20who%20conduct%20elections%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20on%20February%2013%2C%20a%20two-member%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20hearing%20a%20fresh%20petition%20challenging%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20selection%20committee%20refused%20to%20stay%20the%20operation%20of%20the%20law.%20Justices%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%20and%20Dipankar%20Datta%2C%20responding%20to%20the%20plea%20filed%20by%20the%20NGO%2C%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR)%2C%20issued%20a%20notice%20to%20the%20Union%20government%20and%20listed%20the%20next%20hearing%20of%20the%20case%20in%20April%20along%20with%20the%20other%20petitions%20on%20the%20same%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAppearing%20for%20ADR%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Prashant%20Bhushan%20argued%20that%20the%20section%20is%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20ruling%20of%20the%20five-judge%20bench.%20Since%20two%20ECs%20are%20about%20to%20retire%2C%20if%20the%20operation%20of%20the%20law%20is%20not%20stayed%2C%20the%20plea%20would%20become%20infructuous.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Justice%20Khanna%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fsupreme-court-refuses-to-stay-law-on-appointment-of-cec-ecs%2Farticleshow%2F107670602.cms%5C%22%3Estated%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20matter%20which%20can%20be%20decided%20like%20this.%20A%20legislation%20of%20Parliament%20cannot%20be%20stayed%20like%20this.%20We%20have%20to%20examine%20the%20issue%20in%20terms%20of%20power%20of%20judicial%20review.%20We%20will%20hear%20this%20petition%20along%20with%20other%20pending%20petitions%20on%20the%20issue.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20January%2012%2C%20hearing%20a%20petition%20filed%20by%20a%20Congress%20member%20Jaya%20Thakur%20which%20said%20section%207%20and%208%20of%20the%20Act%20did%20not%20provide%20an%20independent%20mechanism%20to%20appoint%20the%20CEC%20and%20the%20ECs%2C%20the%20court%20had%20also%20refused%20to%20stay%20the%20law%20but%20had%20issued%20a%20notice%20to%20the%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20cannot%20stay%20a%20statutory%20amendment.%20Issue%20notice%20is%20returnable%20in%20April%202024%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Khanna%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court%2Fstory%2Fsupreme-court-election-commissioners-appointments-new-law-statutory-amendment-petitions-2487706-2024-01-12%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707893809000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-chief-election-commissioner-act%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20section%20in%20the%20law%20goes%20against%20a%20judgment%20by%20a%20five-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20apex%20court%20in%20March%202022%20which%20disapproved%20of%20the%20system%20brought%20in%20by%20the%20Union%20government.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-chief-election-commissioner-act%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kelvin%20Kangethe%3A%20US%20fugitive%20wante