3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EChina's%20fleet%20of%20civilian%20ships%20earmarked%20for%20war%20is%20unlikely%20to%20successfully%20invade%20Taiwan%20until%20at%20least%202030.%20Still%2C%20Beijing%20is%20making%20steady%20progress%20on%20that%20front%2C%20according%20to%20a%20senior%20analyst.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20military%20conducted%20at%20least%2033%20exercises%20with%20merchant%20vessels%20in%202023%2C%20falling%20short%20of%20the%2038%20such%20activities%20it%20conducted%20in%202022%2C%20wrote%20Michael%20Dahm%2C%20a%20retired%20US%20intelligence%20officer%20who%20is%20now%20a%20senior%20research%20fellow%20at%20the%20Mitchell%20Institute%20for%20Aerospace%20Studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20at%20least%20six%20of%20the%20exercises%20last%20year%20involved%20five%20or%20more%20ships%20in%20coordination%2C%20up%20from%20just%20three%20such%20events%20in%202022%2C%20wrote%20Dahm%20in%20a%20report%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdigital-commons.usnwc.edu%2Fcmsi-maritime-reports%2F35%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%20on%20Thursday%20by%20the%20US%20Naval%20War%20College's%20China%20Maritime%20Studies%20Institute.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20largest%20exercises%20in%202023%20involved%2014%20cargo%20ships%20that%20could%20deliver%20as%20many%20as%201%2C000%20military%20vehicles%20and%202%2C000%20troops%20in%20around%20three%20days%2C%20Dahm%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20civilian%20ships%20are%20mostly%20used%20to%20ferry%20military%20assets%2C%20particularly%20for%20beach%20landings%2C%20in%20exercises%20focused%20along%20the%20Taiwan%20Strait%2C%20Dahm%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20vessels%20are%20typically%20designed%20to%20allow%20wheeled%20vehicles%20to%20roll%20on%20or%20off%20the%20ship%20instead%20of%20being%20lifted%20on%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDahm%20wrote%20that%20last%20year%20also%20involved%20the%20first%20time%20that%20China's%20military%20was%20observed%20using%20large%20deck%20cargo%20ships%2C%20which%20usually%20can%20carry%20fewer%20vehicles%20but%20are%20more%20numerous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20deck%20cargo%20ships%20with%20their%20open%20decks%20may%20not%20be%20suited%20for%20long-distance%20voyages%20with%20military%20vehicles%20and%20personnel%20embarked%2C%20they%20may%20be%20an%20adequate%20and%20plentiful%20choice%20for%20the%20PLA%20to%20lift%20military%20forces%20short%20distances%2C%20such%20as%20across%20the%20Taiwan%20Strait%2C%26quot%3B%20Dahm%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20might%20also%20use%20open-deck%20civilian%20ships%20as%20sea-based%20landing%20pads%20for%20helicopters%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EChina%20'clearly'%20creating%20military%20doctrine%20for%20civilian%20fleet%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20satellite%20imagery%20and%20publicly%20available%20sources%20like%20state%20TV%2C%20Dahm%20recorded%2039%20Chinese%20merchant%20vessels%20supporting%20the%20Chinese%20navy%20over%20812%20ship%20days%20last%20year%2C%20with%20the%20bulk%20of%20activity%20occurring%20in%20the%20late%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%2036%20civilian%20ships%20were%20used%20in%20exercises%20over%20733%20ship%20days%2C%20according%20to%20Dahm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20exercises%20mostly%20involved%20ships%20departing%20from%20and%20landing%20in%20Chinese%20ports%20but%20could%20be%20used%20to%20simulate%20landings%20in%20Taiwan%2C%20Dahm%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20Chinese%20military%20could%20seize%20Taiwan's%20ports%2C%20%26quot%3Bcivil%20maritime%20ships%20might%20then%20surge%20into%20Taiwan%20ports%20and%20harbors%20with%20second%20echelon%20forces%20and%20logistics%2C%26quot%3B%20Dahm%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlternatively%2C%20the%20civilian%20ships%20can%20be%20used%20to%20rapidly%20transport%20military%20resources%20along%20China's%20coast%20during%20war%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Dahm%20also%20cast%20doubt%20on%20the%20likelihood%20that%20China%20can%20successfully%20use%20its%20merchant%20fleet%20anytime%20soon%20