Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20former%20flight%20attendant%20is%20suing%20Singapore%20Airlines%2C%20citing%20an%20injury%20from%20unsafe%20work%20conditions.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDurairaj%20Santiran%20said%20he%20slipped%20on%20a%20grease%20patch%20on%20a%20flight%2C%20and%20is%20now%20suing%20for%20%241.3%20million.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESingapore%20Airlines%2C%20however%2C%20said%20no%20such%20grease%20patch%20existed%20and%20disputed%20his%20claims.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20former%20flight%20attendant%20for%20Singapore%20Airlines%20is%20suing%20the%20carrier%20for%20%241.3%20million%2C%20saying%20it%20failed%20to%20provide%20a%20safe%20working%20environment%20that%20led%20to%20a%20career-ending%20injury.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDurairaj%20Santiran%2C%2036%2C%20appeared%20on%20Tuesday%20in%20Singapore's%20High%20Court%2C%20where%20he%20said%20that%20he%20slipped%20and%20hit%20his%20head%20while%20working%20a%2017-hour%20flight%20in%202019%20because%20of%20a%20grease%20patch%20on%20the%20plane%2C%20local%20media%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20a%20cervical%20disc%20prolapse%20after%20the%20flight%2C%20which%20Durairaj%20said%20eventually%20prevented%20him%20from%20continuing%20work%20as%20a%20cabin%20crew%20member%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.straitstimes.com%2Fsingapore%2Fcourts-crime%2Fex-air-steward-who-slipped-on-grease-patch-and-fell-on-plane-sues-sia-for-178m%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20Singaporean%20daily%20The%20Straits%20Times.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDurairaj%20worked%20as%20a%20flight%20attendant%20for%20Singapore%20Airlines%20from%20April%202016%20to%20April%202021%2C%20according%20to%20the%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20court%2C%20Durairaj%20said%20the%20incident%20occurred%20while%20he%20was%20working%20on%20an%20Airbus%20A350%20flight%20from%20San%20Francisco%20to%20Singapore%2C%20about%20two%20hours%20before%20the%20aircraft%20was%20due%20to%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Durairaj%2C%20he%20initially%20noticed%20a%20three-inch%2C%20colorless%20grease%20patch%20in%20the%20economy%20class%20section%20while%20the%20plane%20was%20about%20to%20depart%20San%20Francisco%2C%20per%20court%20documents%20seen%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20a%20senior%20flight%20attendant%20about%20it%20and%20was%20instructed%20to%20clean%20the%20patch%20with%20disinfectant%20and%20a%20paper%20towel%2C%20though%20he%20was%20unsuccessful%2C%20Durairaj%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20telling%20his%20superior%20that%20the%20patch%20remained%2C%20the%20crew%20tried%20to%20clean%20up%20the%20patch%20one%20more%20time%2C%20but%20couldn't%20get%20rid%20of%20it%2C%20Durairaj%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20flight%20later%20approached%20Singapore%2C%20Durairaj%20slipped%20on%20the%20grease%2C%20struck%20his%20head%20on%20the%20floor%2C%20and%20later%20had%20to%20be%20escorted%20out%20of%20the%20plane%20with%20a%20wheelchair%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHad%20reasonable%20care%20been%20exercised%2C%20the%20grease%20patch%20would%20have%20been%20removed%20or%20such%20steps%20taken%20to%20prevent%20access%20to%20the%20unsafe%20location%2C%26quot%3B%20Durairaj's%20lawyers%20Ramasamy%20Chettiar%20and%20Kasturibai%20Manickam%20said%20in%20his%20opening%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cabin%20crew%20could%20have%20rolled%20a%20pushcart%20on%20top%20of%20the%20grease%20patch%2C%20the%20lawyers%20said%20as%20an%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDurairaj's%20team%20said%20he%20is%20seeking%20%241.3%20million%20in%20compensation%2C%20mostly%20for%20losses%20of%20future%20earnings%20and%20medical%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESingapore%20Airlines'%20lawyers%20disputed%20Durairaj's%20claims%2C%20saying%20that%20no%20such%20grease%20patch%20existed%20and%20that%20Durairaj%20instead%20fell%20at%20another%20section%20of%20the%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDurairaj%20also%20filed%20separate%20work%20injury%20claims%20in%202017%20and%202018%20that%20the%20airline%20did%20not%20contest%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Singapore%20Airlines'%20legal%20team%20in%20its%20opening%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSIA%2C%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20policy%2C%20pays%20all%20valid%20and%20legitimate%20claims%20made%20by%20employees%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20airline's%20lawyers%20said.%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20given%20their%20standing%2C%20reputation%20and%20position%20as%20a%20premier%20airline%20globally%2C%20it%20responds%20to%20invalid%2C%20illegitimate%20and%20false%20claims%2C%20firmly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProceedings%20for%20Durairaj's%20lawsuit%20are%20to%20be%20held%20over%20the%20next%2010%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawyers%20for%20Durairaj%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20a%20case%20still%20being%20heard%20in%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESingapore%20Airlines'%20press%20team%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20sent%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EFebruary%2014%2C%202023%3A%20This%20story%20was%20updated%20to%20reflect%20a%20response%20from%20lawyers%20for%20Durairaj%20Santiran.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflight-attendant-slipped-sues-singapore-airlines-1-million-durairaj-santiran-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707882103000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cc32586fcb546d2d4f8cb9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflight-attendant-slipped-sues-singapore-airlines-1-million-durairaj-santiran-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Durairaj%20Santiran%2C%2036%2C%20said%20he%20slipped%20on%20a%20grease%20patch%20on%20an%20Airbus%20A350%2C%20causing%20an%20injury%20that%20prevents%20him%20from%20working%20as%20a%20flight%20attendant.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mloh%40businessinsider.com%20(Matthew%20Loh)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A64%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflight-attendant-slipped-sues-singapore-airlines-1-million-durairaj-santiran-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Naturopath'%20offers%2070-yr-old%20relief%20from%20pain%2C%20cons%20her%20of%20Rs%2060k%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707881768000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107677400%2Cimgsize-513653.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fmumbai%2Fnaturopath-offers-relief-from-knee-pain-and-cons-elderly-woman-of-rs-60000%2Farticleshow%2F107676821.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20elderly%20homemaker%20in%20Mumbai%20was%20duped%20of%20Rs%2060%2C000%20by%20a%20'naturopath'%20and%20his%20assistant%20who%20offered%20her%20a%20cure%20for%20severe%20knee%20pain.%20The%20duo%2C%20along%20with%20two%20others%2C%20were%20introduced%20to%20the%20complainant.%20The%20naturopath's%20clinic%20in%20Thane%20did%20not%20exist%2C%20leading%20the%20complainant%20to%20file%20a%20police%20complaint.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TNN%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fmumbai%2Fnaturopath-offers-relief-from-knee-pain-and-cons-elderly-woman-of-rs-60000%2Farticleshow%2F107676821.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Investment%20of%20%242%20Trillion%20Per%20Year%20Needed%20to%20Meet%20Global%202030%20Renewable%20Energy%20Target%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F14090239%2Fred-zeppelin-UVGE-o757-g-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKochi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Two%20trillion%20USD%20%E2%80%93%20Rs%202%20two%20lakh%20crore%20%E2%80%93%20a%20year%3A%20that%E2%80%99s%20how%20much%20investment%20is%20required%20to%20meet%20the%20global%202030%20renewable%20energy%20target%2C%20as%20per%20a%20report%20published%20on%20February%2013%20by%20think-tank%20Climate%20Analytics.%20According%20to%20the%20report%2C%20the%20current%20renewable%20energy%20growth%20in%20Asia%20is%20primarily%20due%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20projects%20in%20India%20and%20China%2C%20but%20coal%20projects%20in%20both%20these%20countries%20are%20still%20a%20concern.%20Renewables%20in%20India%2C%20it%20predicts%2C%20will%20likely%20witness%20a%202.9-3.5%20fold%20rise%20by%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20few%20hours%20after%20this%20report%20was%20published%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20announced%20a%20free%20solar%20electricity%20scheme%20for%20residential%20consumers.%20The%20Union%20government%2C%20he%20said%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fnarendramodi%2Fstatus%2F1757308771087306937%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Ea%20series%20of%20posts%20on%20social%20media%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20will%20invest%20over%20Rs%2075%2C000%20crore%20in%20PM%20Surya%20Ghar%3A%20Muft%20Bijli%20Yojana%2C%20a%20project%20that%20encourages%20installation%20rooftop%20solar%20installations%20and%20aims%20to%20provide%20one%20crore%20households%20with%20up%20to%20300%20units%20of%20free%20electricity%20every%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETill%202030%2C%20%2412%20trillion%20for%20renewables%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInvesting%20in%20renewable%20energy%20projects%20to%20decrease%20dependence%20on%20fossil%20fuels%20such%20as%20coal%20and%20gas%20is%20one%20of%20the%20main%20ways%20that%20countries%20attempt%20to%20cut%20down%20on%20excessive%20carbon%20emissions%20to%20decrease%20the%20rate%20of%20global%20warming%20and%20tackle%20climate%20change.%20Globally%2C%20almost%20one-third%20of%20our%20electricity%20comes%20from%20renewables%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fourworldindata.org%2Frenewable-energy%5C%22%3Elatest%20statistics%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Hydropower%20is%20the%20largest%20modern%20renewable%20source%2C%20but%20wind%20and%20solar%20power%20are%20also%20growing%20rapidly.%20Last%20year%2C%20at%20the%20biggest%20climate%20conference%20under%20the%20United%20Nations%20(COP28%2C%20held%20in%20Dubai%2C%20UAE%2C%20in%20November-December)%2C%20one%20of%20the%20improvements%20that%20world%20leaders%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funfccc.int%2Fnews%2Fcop28-agreement-signals-beginning-of-the-end-of-the-fossil-fuel-era%5C%22%3Eagreed%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20was%20a%20renewable%20energy%20target%20for%202030%3A%20tripling%20renewable%20energy%20capacity%2C%20and%20doubling%20energy%20efficiency%20improvements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20achieve%20this%2C%20however%2C%20global%20renewable%20energy%20capacity%20has%20to%20grow%20to%2011.5%20terawatt%20(TW)%2C%20or%203.4%20times%20from%20levels%20as%20of%202022.%20And%20this%20can%20only%20be%20done%20if%20investments%20to%20the%20tune%20of%20%242%20trillion%20a%20year%20are%20spent%20for%20this%20purpose%2C%20as%20per%20a%20report%20by%20think-tank%20Climate%20Analytics.%20However%2C%20the%20statistics%20from%20last%20year%20don%E2%80%99t%20inspire%20much%20hope%3A%20global%20investments%20in%20renewables%20and%20grid%20expansion%20only%20reached%20~%241%20trillion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%2C%20published%20on%20February%2013%2C%20says%20that%20a%20total%20of%20%248%20trillion%20for%20investment%20in%20new%20renewables%2C%20and%20a%20separate%20%244%20trillion%20for%20grid%20and%20storage%20infrastructure%2C%20will%20need%20to%20be%20added%20by%202030%20to%20deliver%20COP28%E2%80%99s%20tripling%20goal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20calculated%20how%20fast%20different%20regions%20(Asia%2C%20Sub-Saharan%20Africa%2C%20the%20Organisation%20for%20Economic%20Co-operation%20and%20Development%20or%20OECD%20nations%2C%20Latin%20America%20and%20the%20Caribbean%2C%20Eurasia%2C%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20North%20Africa%20or%20MENA)%20need%20to%20triple%20global%20renewables%20based%20on%20current%20capacities%20and%20future%20needs.%20The%20OECD%20countries%20(a%20set%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oecd.org%2Fabout%2Fdocument%2Fratification-oecd-convention.htm%5C%22%3E38%20nations%3C%2Fa%3E%20including%20the%20United%20States%20and%20United%20Kingdom)%20are%20not%20on%20track%20to%20meet%20the%20tripling%20goal%3A%20the%20report%20predicts%20that%20this%20group%20will%20fall%20around%20a%20third%20short%20of%20the%20target.%20For%20instance%2C%20renewable%20energy%20shows%20slow%20growth%20in%20Japan%2C%20where%20capacity%20will%20grow%20only%2050%25%20over%20the%20decade%2C%20per%20the%20report.%20In%20fact%2C%20over%20half%20of%20the%20global%20gap%20could%20be%20closed%20through%201.5-aligned%20action%20in%20the%20OECD%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsia%20%E2%80%93%20currently%20home%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmc-cd8320d4-36a1-40ac-83cc-3389-cdn-endpoint.azureedge.net%2F-%2Fmedia%2FFiles%2FIRENA%2FAgency%2FPublication%2F2023%2FMar%2FIRENA_RE_Capacity_Statistics_2023.pdf%3Frev%3Dd2949151ee6a4625b65c82881403c2a7%5C%22%3Erenewable%20energy%20worth%201%2C630%20gigawatts%20(GW)%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20of%202022%20%E2%80%93%20is%20the%20only%20region%20on%20track%20to%20triple%20renewables%20in%20line%20with%201.5%C2%BAC%20because%20renewable%20capacity%20here%20could%20reach%20to%20around%205%20to%205.7%20terawatts%20(around%205-5%2C700%20GW)%20by%202030%20under%20current%20policies%20and%20measures%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAsia%E2%80%99s%20RE%20growth%20mainly%20due%20to%20India%2C%20China%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20largely%20driven%20by%20the%20rate%20of%20renewables%20deployment%20in%20China%20and%20India%2C%20where%20forecasts%20show%20particularly%20strong%20growth%20in%20renewables%20under%20current%20policies%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20India%20and%20China%20account%20for%2090%25%20of%20total%20renewable%20capacity%20in%20Asia.%20So%20despite%20the%20poor%20performance%20of%20other%20Asian%20countries%20such%20as%20South%20Korea%2C%20both%20India%E2%80%99s%20and%20China%E2%80%99s%20strong%20growth%20rates%20%E2%80%9Cdominate%20and%20pull%20the%20whole%20region%20up%20towards%20the%201.5%C2%BAC%20compatible%20benchmark%E2%80%9D%2C%20as%20per%20the%20report.%20The%20report%20also%20predicts%20that%20renewables%20will%20likely%20show%20a%202.9%20to%203.5-fold%20rise%20in%20India%20from%202022%20to%202030.%20And%20slightly%20higher%20in%20China%3A%20by%203.5-3.9%20fold.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Asia%20also%20has%20the%20largest%20pipeline%20for%20gas%20and%20coal-based%20power%20generation.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20vast%20building%20spree%20of%20fossil%20fuel%20infrastructure%20is%20in%20direct%20tension%20with%20the%20global%20commitment%20to%20triple%20renewables%2C%E2%80%9D%20according%20to%20the%20report.%20Continuing%20to%20invest%20in%20fossil%20fuels%20will%20risk%20slowing%20the%20energy%20transition%20(from%20fossil%20fuels%20to%20renewable%20power)%20and%20the%20associated%20climate%20impacts%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20construction%20%E2%80%9Cspree%E2%80%9D%20of%20coal-fired%20power%20plants%20in%20China%20and%20India%20is%20a%20huge%20concern%2C%20as%20per%20the%20report.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20this%20continues%2C%20it%20will%20either%20jeopardise%20a%201.5%C2%BAC-aligned%20power%20sector%20transition%2C%20or%20create%20large-scale%20stranded%20assets%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20has%20predicted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20continues%20to%20invest%20in%20coal-based%20power%20plants.%20%3Cem%3EMoneyControl%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20that%20data%20from%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Coal%20showed%20that%20domestic%20coal-based%20power%20generation%20from%20April%20to%20October%202023%20reached%20686.7%20billion%20units%20(BU)%2C%20reflecting%20an%208.88%25%20increase%20when%20compared%20to%20the%20previous%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20there%20are%20plans%20for%20more%3A%20India%20will%20start%20operating%20new%20coal-fired%20power%20plants%20with%20a%20combined%20capacity%20of%2013.9%20gigawatts%20(GW)%20this%20year%2C%20its%20power%20ministry%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Fenergy%2Findia-increase-coal-fired-capacity-2024-by-most-least-6-years-2024-02-01%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520planned%2520coal%252Dfired%2520capacity%2C26.4%2520GW%2520currently%2520being%2520constructed.%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EReuters%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20on%20February%201%20this%20year.%20This%2C%20as%20per%20the%20news%20report%2C%20will%20be%20the%20highest%20annual%20increase%20in%20at%20least%20six%20years.%20The%20ministry%20hopes%20to%20add%20at%20least%2053.6%20GW%20of%20coal-fired%20power%20capacity%20over%20the%20eight%20years%20ending%20March%202032%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20the%2026.4%20GW%20currently%20being%20constructed%2C%20the%20Ministry%20told%20%3Cem%3EReuters%3C%2Fem%3E.%20However%2C%20this%20bodes%20disaster%20from%20a%20renewable%20energy%20point%20of%20view%3B%20and%20we%20may%20not%20even%20need%20it%2C%20if%20renewable%20energy%20catches%20on%20at%20its%20current%20pace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWith%20Asia%E2%80%99s%20%5Bforecasted%5D%20strong%20growth%20in%20renewables%20capacity%2C%20new%20fossil%20fuel%20plants%20are%20not%20needed%20to%20meet%20electricity%20demand%20growth%20and%20should%20be%20avoided%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Climate%20Analytics%20report%20recommended.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPM%20announces%20Har%20Ghar%20Bijli%20Yojana%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20same%20day%20that%20the%20report%20was%20published%2C%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20announced%2C%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fnarendramodi%2Fstatus%2F1757308771087306937%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Ea%20series%20of%20posts%20on%20social%20media%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20scheme%20for%20free%20solar%20electricity%20%E2%80%9Cto%20further%20sustainable%20development%20and%20people%E2%80%99s%20wellbeing%E2%80%9D%2C%20called%20the%20PM%20Surya%20Ghar%3A%20Muft%20Bijli%20Yojana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%2C%20Modi%20said%2C%20will%20invest%20over%20Rs%2075%2C000%20crore%20into%20this%20free%20solar%20electricity%20scheme%20to%20encourage%20the%20installation%20of%20rooftop%20solar%20systems%2C%20and%20aims%20to%20light%20up%20one%20crore%20households%20by%20providing%20up%20to%20300%20units%20of%20free%20electricity%20every%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFrom%20substantive%20subsidies%2C%20which%20will%20be%20given%20directly%20to%20people%E2%80%99s%20bank%20accounts%2C%20to%20heavily%20concessional%20bank%20loans%2C%20the%20Central%20Government%20will%20ensure%20that%20there%20is%20no%20cost%20burden%20on%20the%20people%2C%E2%80%9D%20Modi%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fnarendramodi%2Fstatus%2F1757308773297709434%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Etweeted%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20Twitter.%20%E2%80%9CAll%20stakeholders%20will%20be%20integrated%20to%20a%20National%20Online%20Portal%20which%20will%20further%20convenience.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPer%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmsuryaghar.gov.in%2Fpdf%2FCFA_structure20240213.pdf%5C%22%3Escheme%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20residential%20households%20can%20avail%20subsidies%20of%20Rs%2030%2C000%20per%20kilowatt%20for%20rooftop%20solar%20installations%20of%20up%20to%20two%20kW%3B%20Rs%2018%2C000%20per%20kW%20for%20additional%20capacity%20of%20up%20to%20three%20kW%3B%20and%20the%20subsidy%20for%20systems%20larger%20than%203%20kW%20will%20be%20capped%20at%20Rs%2078%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20popularise%20this%20scheme%20at%20the%20grassroots%2C%20the%20government%20will%20incentivise%20urban%20local%20bodies%20and%20panchayats%20to%20promote%20rooftop%20solar%20systems%20in%20their%20jurisdictions%2C%20Modi%20said.%20The%20scheme%20would%20increase%20income%2C%20decrease%20power%20bills%20and%20generate%20employment%2C%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fnarendramodi%2Fstatus%2F1757308775399096596%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Eadded%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLet%E2%80%99s%20boost%20solar%20power%20and%20sustainable%20progress.%20I%20urge%20all%20residential%20consumers%2C%20especially%20youngsters%2C%20to%20strengthen%20the%20PM%20%E2%80%93%20Surya%20Ghar%3A%20Muft%20Bijli%20Yojana%20by%20applying%20at-%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmsuryaghar.gov.in%2F%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Fpmsuryaghar.gov.in%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fnarendramodi%2Fstatus%2F1757308777466937378%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Etweeted%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20scheme%20is%20the%20%3Cem%3Emuft%20bijli%3C%2Fem%3E%20(free%20electricity)%20project%20that%20finance%20minister%20Nirmala%20Sitharaman%20announced%20in%20her%20interim%20budget%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiabudget.gov.in%2Fdoc%2Fbudget_speech.pdf%5C%22%3Espeech%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20February%201%20this%20year.%20Sitharaman%20had%20said%20that%20the%20scheme%20can%20provide%20savings%20of%20up%20to%20Rs%2015%2C000-18%2C000%20annually%20for%20households%2C%20from%20free%20solar%20electricity%20and%20by%20selling%20the%20surplus%20to%20the%20distribution%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSome%20broader%20level%20schemes%20of%20providing%20rooftop%20solar%20for%201%20crore%20households%20with%20300%20units%20of%20free%20electricity%20and%20excess%20to%20be%20sold%20to%20discoms%2C%20are%20positive%20measures%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Vibhuti%20Garg%2C%20director%20%E2%80%93%20South%20Asia%2C%20Institute%20for%20Energy%20Economics%20and%20Financial%20Analysis%2C%20while%20commenting%20on%20the%20budget%20speech%20on%20February%201%20to%20Climate%20Trends%2C%20a%20research-based%20consulting%20and%20capacity%20building%20initiative.%20%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20net%20metering%20policies%20are%20not%20favourable%20in%20every%20state%20where%20consumers%20can%20gain%20from%20selling%20electricity%20back%20to%20the%20grid%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENet%20metering%20policies%2C%20which%20vary%20across%20states%2C%20are%20a%20billing%20mechanism%20that%20credits%20solar%20energy%20system%20owners%20for%20the%20electricity%20they%20add%20to%20the%20grid.%20India%E2%80%99s%20target%20is%20to%20install%2040%2C000%20megawatts%20MW%20(or%204%20gigawatts%20GW)%20of%20rooftop%20solar%20power%20by%202026.%20According%20to%20one%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbridgetoindia.com%2Freport%2Findia-solar-rooftop-map-june-2023%2F%5C%22%3Eestimate%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20India%20has%20reached%20a%20total%20rooftop%20solar%20capacity%20of%2012%2C762%20MW%20(12.7%20GW)%20as%20of%20the%20end%20of%20June%202023.%20Of%20this%2C%20residential%20rooftop%20solar%20only%20amounts%20to%202.7%20GW.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707881601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F14090239%2Fred-zeppelin-UVGE-o757-g-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenergy%2Finvestment-of-2-trillion-per-year-needed-to-meet-global-2030-renewable-energy-target%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20India%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20has%20just%20announced%20a%20free%20solar%20electricity%20scheme%20which%20will%20provide%20~one%20crore%20households%20up%20to%20300%20units%20of%20free%20solar%20energy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenergy%2Finvestment-of-2-trillion-per-year-needed-to-meet-global-2030-renewable-energy-target%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sergey%20Brin's%20ex-wife%20was%20the%20primary%20funder%20of%20an%20RFK%20Jr.-supporting%20Super%20Bowl%20ad%20panned%20by%20some%20in%20the%20Kennedy%20family%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Nicole%20Shanahan%20in%20a%20black%20dress%20smiles%20at%20the%20camera%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cbfce7f533b039a883643f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENicole%20Shanahan%20he