E%3Cspan%3EPakistanis%20get%20excited%20easily%3A%20almost%20all%20our%20elections%20are%20called%20%E2%80%98historic%2C%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98game%20changers%2C%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98significant.%E2%80%99%20Of%20course%2C%20every%20election%20is%20important%2C%20as%20it%20gives%20an%20opportunity%20for%20the%20political%20landscape%20to%20change.%20But%20it%20is%20the%20unchanging%20part%20of%20the%20elections%20which%20has%20caused%20and%20continues%20to%20create%20problems%20for%20the%20country.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20February%208%2C%202024%20elections%20were%2C%20as%20all%20elections%20go%2C%20important.%20Nearly%2050%25%20of%20the%20electorate%20exercised%20their%20democratic%20right%20and%20the%20candidates%20backed%20by%20the%20incarcerated%20Pakistan%20Tehreek-i-Insaf%20(PTI)%20leader%20Imran%20Khan%20bagged%20the%20largest%20number%20of%20seats%20in%20the%20national%20assembly%20despite%20months%20of%20repression.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EPeople%20are%20already%20singing%20praises%20for%20the%20%E2%80%98youth%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20those%20who%20have%20come%20of%20age%20since%20the%20last%20election%20of%202018%2C%20of%20voting%20in%20large%20numbers%20for%20Imran%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20nominees.%20Savvy%20analysts%20have%20lauded%20that%20this%20is%20is%20a%20big%20slap%20on%20the%20face%20of%20the%20(military)%20establishment%2C%20and%20claimed%20that%20people%20have%20showed%20their%20mettle%20against%20all%20adversity.%20So%20far%20so%20good.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20the%202024%20election%20results%20are%20almost%20same%20as%20the%202018%20elections.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202018%2C%20the%20establishment-supported%20PTI%20won%20the%20largest%20number%20of%20seats%20followed%20by%20the%20then%20disqualified%20and%20later%20imprisoned%20Nawaz%20Sharif%E2%80%99s%20Pakistan%20Muslim%20League%20Nawaz%20(PMLN)%2C%20and%20the%20Bhutto-Zardari%20Pakistan%20Peoples%20Party%20(PPP).%20In%202018%2C%20the%20establishment%20cobbled%20together%20a%20coalition%20for%20the%20PTI%2C%20and%20then%20in%202022%2C%20after%20Imran%E2%80%99s%20fall%20from%20grace%2C%20that%20coalition%20broke%20and%20a%20PMLN-PPP%20led%20combine%20came%20to%20power%20for%202022-2023.%20Today%2C%20it%20seems%20that%20the%20same%20combine%20might%20come%20back%20to%20power%2C%20albeit%20with%20a%20few%20more%20seats%20than%20last%20time.%20The%20vote%20shares%20of%20PTI%2C%20PMLN%20and%20PP%20are%20also%20largely%20the%20same%20as%202018.%20The%20people%20who%20ultimately%20decided%20the%20government%20in%202018%2C%202022%20and%202024%20are%20also%20the%20same.%20So%20nothing%E2%80%99s%20changed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPakistan%E2%80%99s%20constant%20has%20been%20the%20role%20of%20the%20civil-military%20establishment%20since%20its%20inception%20in%201947.%20The%20first%20time%20a%20government%20was%20unceremoniously%20dismissed%20was%20on%20August%2022%2C%201947%2C%20barely%20a%20week%20after%20independence%20when%20the%20elected%20Congress%20government%20in%20the%20erstwhile%20North%20West%20Frontier%20Province%20was%20removed%20by%20executive%20order%20and%20replaced%20by%20a%20Muslim%20League%20ministry.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20the%20Congress%20had%2030%20seats%20in%20an%20assembly%20of%2050%2C%20with%2019%20Muslim%20seats%2C%20while%20the%20Muslim%20League%20only%20had%2017%20Muslim%20seats.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fpakistan-elections-in-the-face-of-a-hegemonic-establishment-people-have-shown-the-way%5C%22%3EPakistan%20Elections%3A%20In%20the%20Face%20of%20a%20Hegemonic%20Establishment%2C%20People%20Have%20Shown%20the%20Way%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20assembly%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20dissolved%20to%20get%20a%20fresh%20mandate%20and%20no%20session%20was%20even%20called%20for%20seven%20months%20for%20the%20new%20government%20to%20prove%20its%20majority.%20Thereafter%2C%20as%20my%20work%20on%20the%20integration%20of%20the%20Pakistan%20princely%20states%20has%20shown%2C%20the%20establishment%E2%80%99s%20control%20steadily%20increased%20and%2C%20by%20the%20end%20of%201948%2C%20the%20bureaucracy%20and%20the%20military%20directly%20controlled%20over%20half%20the%20landmass%20of%20the%20then%20western%20Pakistan.%20The%20executive%20dismissal%20of%20the%20first%20constituent%20assembly%20of%20Pakistan%20and%20the%20resultant%20Maulvi%20Tamizuddin%20case%20in%201955%20then%20sealed%20the%20deal%20against%20politicians.%20Thus%2C%20within%20the%20first%20decade%2C%20Pakistan%20set%20in%20a%20certain%20mould%20where%20despite%20various%20attempts%20over%20the%20years%2C%20the%20basic%20equation%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20changed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPakistan%20has%20never%20had%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20or%20so%20of%20even%20quasi-democratic%20government%20in%20its%20history.%20Thus%2C%20after%20two%20full%20parliamentary%20tenures%20between%202008-13%2C%20and%202013-18%2C%20the%20time%20was%20nigh%20for%20the%20establishment%20to%20wrest%20some%20control%20back.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20restoration%20of%20full%20parliamentary%20government%20and%20the%20(almost)%20restoration%20of%20full%20provincial%20autonomy%20through%20the%2018%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Amendment%20in%202010%20had%20created%20structural%20problems%20for%20the%20establishment%20which%20they%20wanted%20fixed.%20Hence%2C%20an%20experiment%20was%20launched%20in%20the%20political%20arena%20by%20the%20establishment%20%E2%80%93%20Imran%20Khan%2C%20just%20like%20they%20had%20done%20multiple%20times%20in%20the%20past%2C%20from%20Zulfikar%20Ali%20Bhutto%20in%20the%201950s%2C%20to%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20in%20the%201980s.%20With%20Sharif%20forced%20out%20of%20the%20political%20arena%20through%20dubious%20cases%20and%20his%20party%20under%20extreme%20pressure%20%E2%80%93%20not%20unlike%20the%20PTI%20this%20time%2C%20Imran%20Khan%20was%20installed%20as%20the%20prime%20minister%20in%202018%2C%20heading%20a%20shaky%20and%20a%20bare%20majority%20coalition%2C%20where%20the%20only%20glue%20came%20from%20the%20establishment%20%E2%80%93%20a%20hybrid%20regime%2C%20if%20you%20will.%20With%20Imran%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20fall%20from%20favour%20in%202022%20came%20the%20now%20infamous%20%E2%80%98Vote%20of%20No%20Confidence%E2%80%99%20in%20April%2C%20and%20a%20new%20approved%20coalition%20with%20PMLN-PPP%20in%20the%20lead%20which%20then%20completed%20the%20parliamentary%20term.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20the%20fact%20that%20Pakistan%20has%20now%20completed%20three%20parliamentary%20terms%20of%20five%20years%20each%2C%20democracy%20has%20not%20progressed%20in%20the%20country.%20All%20the%20gains%20of%202008-2018%20have%20been%20systematically%20lost%20between%202018-2024%2C%20and%20it%20seems%20that%20things%20might%20get%20worse.%20The%20reason%20persists%2C%20and%20its%20only%20solution%20%E2%80%93%20the%20emergence%20of%20actual%20anti-establishment%20politics%2C%20still%20evades%20the%20political%20landscape.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESimply%20put%2C%20unless%20major%20political%20parties%20agree%20and%20persist%20in%20the%20exclusion%20of%20all%20non-political%20forces%20from%20the%20governance%20of%20Pakistan%2C%20conditions%20will%20never%20improve.%20Some%20analysts%20have%20argued%20that%20PTI%E2%80%99s%20votes%20and%20seats%20have%20shown%20that%20the%20country%20has%20reached%20a%20tipping%20point%3A%20but%20has%20it%3F%20Pakistan%20has%20had%20several%20anti-establishment%20moments%20in%20the%20past%20but%20none%20have%20been%20lasting.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fpakistan-election-pml-n-hold-talks-with-ppp-us-uk-eu-express-concerns-over-process%5C%22%3EPakistan%20Election%3A%20PML-N%20Hold%20Talks%20with%20PPP%3B%20US%2C%20UK%2C%20EU%20Raise%20Concerns%20Over%20Irregularities%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFrom%20Benazir%20Bhutto%E2%80%99s%20historic%20win%20in%201988%20to%20become%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20first%20Muslim%20woman%20prime%20minister%2C%20to%20Nawaz%20and%20Benazir%20signing%20the%20%E2%80%98Charter%20to%20Democracy%E2%80%99%20in%202006%2C%20to%20Nawaz%E2%80%99s%20daring%20slogan%20in%202018%2C%20%E2%80%98Vote%20ko%20Izzat%20doh%E2%80%99%20(Give%20Respect%20to%20the%20Vote).%20We%20have%20been%20there%2C%20and%20then%20come%20back.%20But%20will%202024%20buck%20the%20trend%3F%20I%20fear%20not.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20fears%20rest%20on%20three%20premises.%20First%2C%20the%20anti-establishment%20narrative%20carved%20out%20by%20the%20PMLN%20and%20PPP%20under%20the%20Charter%20of%20Democracy%20lasted%20just%20over%20a%20decade.%20Once%20out%20of%20power%20in%20the%20centre%20in%202018%2C%20both%20could%20not%20withstand%20the%20onslaught%20of%20the%20Imran%20years%20and%20were%20more%20than%20happy%20to%20return%20to%20the%20establishments%E2%80%99%20loving%20arms%20in%202022.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20flip%2C%20by%20parties%20which%20have%20suffered%20in%20the%20past%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20establishment%2C%20should%20not%20be%20taken%20lightly%20and%20needs%20deeper%20analysis%20as%20it%20exhibits%20the%20limitations%20of%20being%20anti-establishment%20in%20Pakistan.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESecondly%2C%20the%20PTI%20is%20only%20anti-establishment%20because%20the%20establishment%20is%20against%20Imran%20Khan.%20If%20the%20tables%20turn%2C%20the%20PTI%20will%20be%20more%20than%20happy%20to%20return%20to%20the%20fold.%20Thirdly%2C%20politics%20is%20fast%20changing%20in%20the%20country%2C%20where%20populism%20and%20neo-fascism%20are%20gaining%20strength.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20PTI%20has%20now%20developed%20into%20a%20party%20which%20Pakistan%20has%20never%20seen%20before.%20While%20the%20party%20is%20no%20doubt%20popular%2C%20its%20narrative%20is%20deeply%20populist%2C%20divisive%2C%20and%20has%20strong%20fascist%20tendencies.%20Unlike%20other%20major%20parties%2C%20it%20has%20a%20deep%20sense%20of%20self-righteousness%2C%20and%20a%20complete%20rejection%20of%20the%20legitimacy%20of%20anyone%20else.%20These%20twin%20factors%20make%20it%20impossible%20to%20work%20with%20any%20other%20major%20political%20party%20and%20prevent%20its%20current%20anti-establishment%20tilt%20from%20being%20anything%20more%20than%20self-serving.%20Thus%2C%20unless%20there%20is%20a%20broad%2C%20cooperative%20and%20lasting%20anti-establishment%20political%20consensus%2C%20things%20will%20not%20change.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOver%20the%20past%20year%2C%20a%20former%20prime%20minister%20and%20finance%20minister%20of%20Pakistan%2C%20Shahid%20Khaqan%20Abbasi%20and%20Miftah%20Ismail%20respectively%2C%20have%20been%20conducting%20seminars%20across%20the%20county%20called%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DzNfboMSJkRE%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EReimagining%20Pakistan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%E2%80%99%20Speaking%20at%20the%20Lahore%20ThinkFest%20a%20few%20weeks%20ago%2C%20they%20discussed%20the%20contour%20of%20a%20new%20%E2%80%98social%20contract%E2%80%99%20which%20Pakistan%20needs%20to%20emerge%20out%20of%20this%20quagmire.%20But%20this%20is%20easier%20said%20than%20done.%20New%20social%20contracts%20are%20usually%20the%20results%20of%20either%20revolutions%20or%20great%20social%20upheavals%2C%20both%20of%20which%20seem%20unlikely%20in%20Pakistan%20in%20the%20near%20future.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EYaqoob%20Khan%20Bangash%20is%20a%20historian%20based%20in%20Lahore%2C%20Pakistan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707877839000%2C%22visual%22%3A%